The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 3-0 win for England

London: England scored a morale-boosting 3-0 win over Israel at Wembley Stadium on Saturday to improve their hopes of qualifying for next years European Championship finals. 

Shaun Wright-Phillips opened the scoring in the 20th minute, Michael Owen added a second in the 49th and Micah Richards headed home in the 66th as England moved up from fourth to third in group E. 

England, hit by a series of injuries to key players including Wayne Rooney, David Beckham and Owen Hargreaves, recorded their first win at the newly-rebuilt stadium after drawing with Brazil and losing to Germany in friendlies. 

Israels first goal attempt was an off-target shot by Yuval Shpungin after 74 minutes.

 (Reuters) 




